[35mam-okay[0m('1')                                                                                                               [35mam-okay[0m('1')

[32mNAME[0m
       [35mam-okay[0m (version 3.0.6) .

[32mDESCRIPTION[0m
       [35mam-okay[0m is a program that allows to an user to copy and cut files or
       directories dynamically.
       You can do an action in a terminal and finalize this action in another terminal
       with the same user .

[32mOVERVIEW[0m
       @requires This program allows to an user to execute some actions(see the precondition)
       that can be very useful (First of all, this program is written for the
       Ve-Quantic members) .

[32mREQUIRES[0m
       @requires The only options supported are [ [36m--copy,[0m [36m--cut,[0m [36m--paste-copy,[0m [36m--paste-cut,[0m [36m--array,[0m
                                                  [36m--index,[0m [36m--put,[0m [36m--stat-copy,[0m [36m--stat-cut,[0m [36m--stat,[0m
                                                  [36m--reset,[0m [36m--doc,[0m [36m--help[0m ]
       && the command [35mam-okay[0m has to have at least one option then(if that's your goal) the target
       directory/directories or file/files.
           Example : [35mam-okay[0m [36m--copy[0m [36m<myTargetDir>[0m (for sure without the hyphens)
       && with the option [36m<[36m--index>[0m[0m there is a limit at the level of the indexes
       and the indexes have to be a positive integer(min 0 and max 3)
       && the [36m<[36m--index>,[0m[0m  [36m<[36m--put>[0m[0m and [36m<[36m--stat>[0m[0m options are linked to
       the [36m<[36m--array>[0m[0m option
       && [36m<[36m--stat-copy>[0m[0m is linked to the [36m<[36m--copy>[0m[0m option
       && [36m<[36m--stat-cut>[0m[0m is linked to the [36m<[36m--cut>[0m[0m option
       && the [36m<[36m--reset>[0m[0m option has to follow by the [36mrequest[0m value .

[32mSYNOPSIS[0m
       [35mam-okay[0m [options] [target-dir | target-file | target-dirs | target-files ]

[32mOPTIONS[0m
       [36m--copy[0m        type(string) // This option allows to copy the target file/files or
                     directory/directories(that are its targets), you can use the joker [36m<*>[0m to indicate
                     everything that is in the current directory .
                          [36mEx : [0m[35mam-okay[0m [36m--copy[0m [36m<your-target-dir-or-file>[0m [36m<..>[0m

       [36m--cut[0m         type(string) // This option allows to cut the target file/files or
                     directory/directories(that are its targets), you can use the joker [36m<*>[0m to indicate
                     everything that is in the current directory .
                          [36mEx : [0m[35mam-okay[0m [36m--cut[0m [36m<your-target-dir-or-file>[0m [36m<..>[0m

       [36m--paste-copy[0m  type(string) // This option allows to paste a copy action .
                          [36mEx : [0m[35mam-okay[0m [36m--paste-copy[0m [36m<your-target-directory>[0m
                     You can use the dot [36m<.>[0m to indicate the current directory. This option([36m--paste-copy)[0m is
                     linked to the [36m<[36m--copy>[0m[0m option .
                     Use case :
                         Action 1 ->  [36mEx : [0m[35mam-okay[0m [36m--copy[0m [36m<my-file>[0m
                         Action 2 ->  [36mEx : [0m[35mam-okay[0m [36m--paste-copy[0m [36m<my-target-dir>[0m

       [36m--paste-cut[0m   type(string) // This option allows to paste a cut action .
                             [36mEx : [0m[35mam-okay[0m [36m--paste-cut[0m [36m<your-target-directory>[0m
                     You can use the dot [36m<.>[0m to indicate the current directory. This option([36m--paste-cut)[0m is
                     linked to the [36m<[36m--cut>[0m[0m option .
                     Use case :
                         Action 1 ->  [36mEx : [0m[35mam-okay[0m [36m--cut[0m [36m<my-file>[0m
                         Action 2 ->  [36mEx : [0m[35mam-okay[0m [36m--paste-cut[0m [36m<my-target-dir>[0m

       [36m--array[0m       type(String> // This option allows to copy or cut files or directories in a
                     separate way(form of index) .
                          [36mEx : [0m[35mam-okay[0m [36m--array[0m [36m--index[0m 0 [36m--copy[0m [36m<file-1>[0m [36m<dir-1>[0m [36m<dir-2>[0m [36m<..>[0m
                     For pasting according to the previous action you have to do :
                          [36mEx : [0m[35mam-okay[0m [36m--array[0m [36m--index[0m 0 [36m--put[0m [36m<your-target-dir>[0m

       [36m--index[0m       type(String> // This option allows to target the index of the array .
                     Use case :
                          [36mEx : [0m[35mam-okay[0m [36m--array[0m [36m--index[0m 0 [36m--copy[0m [36m<file-1>[0m [36m<dir-1>[0m [36m<dir-2>[0m [36m<..>[0m
                          [36mEx : [0m[35mam-okay[0m [36m--array[0m [36m--index[0m 1 [36m--put[0m [36m<your-target-dir>[0m
                         Note :
                             1.0 You can not do this ->  [36mEx : [0m[35mam-okay[0m [36m--array[0m [36m--index[0m 0-1 [36m--copy[0m [36m<your-dir>[0m [36m<..>[0m
                             1.1 You can do this     ->  [36mEx : [0m[35mam-okay[0m [36m--array[0m [36m--index[0m 0-1 [36m--put[0m [36m<your-dir>[0m
                             1.2 In the previous action(1.1) the [36m<[36m--put>[0m[0m option will manage all actions with the
                                 [36m<[36m--array>[0m[0m option that associated with the [36m<[36m--index>,[0m[0m [36m<[36m--copy>[0m[0m
                                 and [36m<[36m--cut>[0m[0m options .

       [36m--put[0m         type(string) // This option allows to put directory/directories or file/files that have
                     been targeted by the [36m<[36m--array>[0m[0m option associated with the [36m<[36m--copy>[0m[0m
                     and [36m<[36m--cut>[0m[0m options .
                     Use case :
                          [36mEx : [0m[35mam-okay[0m [36m--array[0m [36m--index[0m 0 [36m--put <your_dir>[0m
                          [36mEx : [0m[35mam-okay[0m [36m--array[0m [36m--index[0m 0-3 [36m--put <your_dir>[0m // The indexes between `0` and `3`.
                          [36mEx : [0m[35mam-okay[0m [36m--array[0m [36m--index[0m 0,3 [36m--put <your_dir>[0m // The index `0` and `3`.

       [36m--stat-copy[0m   type(string) // To see the status of an action done with the [36m<[36m--copy>[0m[0m option as first
                     parameter .
                          [36mEx : [0m[35mam-okay[0m [36m--stat-copy[0m

       [36m--stat-cut[0m    type(string) // To see the status of an action done with the [36m<[36m--cut>[0m[0m option as first
                     parameter .
                          [36mEx : [0m[35mam-okay[0m [36m--stat-cut[0m

       [36m--stat[0m        type(string) // To see the status of an action done with the [36m<[36m--array>[0m[0m option as first
                     parameter and along with the [36m<[36m--copy>[0m[0m and [36m<[36m--cut>[0m[0m options or between them .
                     Use case :
                          [36mEx : [0m[35mam-okay[0m [36m--array[0m [36m--index[0m 0 [36m--stat[0m
                          [36mEx : [0m[35mam-okay[0m [36m--array[0m [36m--index[0m 0-2 [36m--stat[0m // The indexes between `0` and `2`.
                          [36mEx : [0m[35mam-okay[0m [36m--array[0m [36m--index[0m 0,2 [36m--stat[0m // The index `0` and `2`.


       [36m--reset[0m       type(string) // To reset your desired action(s), there will be a prompt for the
                     possible choices (note : you have to enter expressly the `request` word) .
                          [36mEx : [0m[35mam-okay[0m [36m--reset[0m [36mrequest[0m

       [36m--doc[0m         type(string) // To see the documentation of the program [35mam-okay[0m
                          [36mEx : [0m[35mam-okay[0m [36m--doc[0m

       [36m--help[0m        type(sting) // To get help
                          [36mEx : [0m[35mam-okay[0m [36m--help[0m

[32mENSURE[0m
       @ensure Successfully execution if the precondition is satisfied. That is to say, with
       the above options and the appropriated sequences linked to these options .

[32mNOTE[0m
       @note This program depends of some programs, these programs are required in the global
       package [35mam-okay[0m .
       Once you have pasted files or directories with the [36m<[36m--paste-copy>[0m[0m option, you can paste
       again the same files/dirs with the same option [36m<[36m--paste-copy>.[0m[0m For sure an action done
       by [36m<[36m--copy>[0m[0m option requires the [36m<[36m--paste-copy>[0m[0m option for pasting, and an action
       done by [36m<[36m--cut>[0m[0m option requires [36m<[36m--paste-cut>[0m[0m option for pasting. The two
       [ [36m--copy,[0m [36m--cut[0m ] options have different hash codes .
       When you execute the command [35mam-okay[0m , the command in question works with the profile
       it was run with. Running it with different profiles will result in different scenarios, because
       for the program each user is different. So when you realise an action, make sure to conserve
       the same profile to paste .
       A progress bar will be displayed to indicate the move and copy status when you execute the
       command [35mam-okay[0m with the [36m<[36m--paste-copy>,[0m[0m [36m<[36m--paste-cut>[0m[0m and [36m<[36m--put>[0m[0m options .

